// General hints: The engine is "ROEngine" in the console, and the game memory is ROEngine.getGameMemory().
// The game memory is broken up into the major regions (world, circuit, robots) which are each uint8 arrays.
// For more information about the known structure of the data within, check "rodata.h" in the C++ source.

// Minimal world file built from scratch in a hex editor, with empty sprites and with rooms labeled.
// (Loads in Innovation Lab; change the last byte to load as a particular game level.)
% echo https\://robotodyssey.online/\#$((echo -ne \\x11; cat minimal.lsv | zstd) | base64 -w0)
https://robotodyssey.online/#

// Sound test.. this only works in GAME.EXE, I've hardcoded its addresses because the
// compile-time pattern matching and symbol export doesn't have anything for sound yet.
// The PC speaker engine uses an array of room-specific sound sources or channels, which
// are typically filled from a table of canned effect parameters. Effect numbers, indexing
// into these tables, are 0 through 27.
function soundTest(effect_id) {
  var world = ROEngine.getGameMemory().world;
  var current_room = world[0x300];
  var mem = ROEngine.getMemory();
  var sound_source_id = --mem[0x4b6a];
  var sound_effect_mode = mem[0xd28b + effect_id];
  var sound_effect_duration = mem[0xd2a7 + effect_id];
  var sound_effect_sweep = mem[0xd2c3 + effect_id];
  var sound_effect_pitch = mem[0xd2df + effect_id];
  mem[0x4b42 + sound_source_id] = sound_effect_duration;
  mem[0x4b4a + sound_source_id] = sound_effect_sweep;
  mem[0x4b52 + sound_source_id] = sound_effect_pitch;
  mem[0x4b5a + sound_source_id] = sound_effect_mode;
  mem[0x4b62 + sound_source_id] = current_room;
  console.log("sound", { effect_id, sound_source_id, current_room,
    sound_effect_mode, sound_effect_duration, sound_effect_sweep, sound_effect_pitch })
}
// Cycle through sounds in a loop
{
  var next_effect = 0;
  const interval = 3000;
  setInterval(() => {
    soundTest(next_effect);
    next_effect = (next_effect + 1) % 28;
  }, interval);
}

// Code to generate the circular sprite:
for (var spr=0;spr<4;spr++)
  for (var y=0;y<16;y++) {
    var byt=0;
    for (var x=0;x<7;x++) {
      var sx=x; if (spr&1) sx = 7-sx;
      var sy=y; if (spr&2) sy = 15-sy;
      if ((Math.pow(sx,2)+Math.pow(sy*0.4,2))<40)
        byt |= 1<<x;
    }
    ROEngine.getGameMemory().world[0xa00+((spr+216)<<4)+y]=byt;
  }

// If you want to cheat your way through walls a little, this binds CTRL-Arrow keys to directly nudge the position
// of the player. By holding down CTRL while navigating with the arrows, the nudge will override collision detection.

document.body.addEventListener('keydown', function (e) {
        if (e.ctrlKey && e.code === 'ArrowLeft') ROEngine.getGameMemory().world[0x400]--;
        if (e.ctrlKey && e.code === 'ArrowRight') ROEngine.getGameMemory().world[0x400]++;
        if (e.ctrlKey && e.code === 'ArrowDown') ROEngine.getGameMemory().world[0x500]--;
        if (e.ctrlKey && e.code === 'ArrowUp') ROEngine.getGameMemory().world[0x500]++;
})

// Another cheat code: move every item in the current room to the player's position
// (This iterates over all items, but we could also have walked the room linked list)

for (var o=0;o<0x100;o++) { if (world[0x300+o]==world[0x300]){ world[0x400+o]=world[0x400];world[0x500+o]=world[0x500]; }}

// The game actually has an no-collision cheat built-in, if you want something a little heavier than the nudge.
// This Javascript function writes an undocumented option to a file normally used for joystick configuration.
// After it's set, you can reload/restart the game and use CTRL-E to disable or enable collision detection.

ROEngine.setCheatsEnabled(true)

// Save file screenshot testing

function sshot(f) {
	var c = document.createElement('canvas');
	c.width = 644; c.height = 388;
	c.getContext('2d').putImageData(ROEngine.screenshotSaveFile(f, false), 2, 2);
	var im = document.createElement('img');
	im.width = 80; im.height = 60;
	im.src = c.toDataURL();
	document.body.appendChild(im);
}
for (var i = 0; i < 30; i++) sshot(ROEngine.getSaveFile());

// Microphone spectrum analyzer input

ROEngine.setSpeed(4.0);
actx = new AudioContext();
an = new AnalyserNode(actx, { fftSize: 2048, smoothingTimeConstant: 0.5, minDecibels: -100.0, maxDecibels: -10.0 });
navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({audio: true}).then(function (s) {actx.createMediaStreamSource(s).connect(an)});
w=ROEngine.getGameMemory().world;
robots=ROEngine.getGameMemory().robots;
buf=new Uint8Array(2048);
function render(c) {
	for (var r of robots) r.state[24] = 15;
	an.getByteFrequencyData(buf);
	c.fillStyle = "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8)";
	var bsize = an.frequencyBinCount / 8;
	for (var bin = 0; bin < 8; bin++) {
		var s = 0;
		for (var i = bin*bsize; i < (bin+1)*bsize; i++) s += buf[i];
		s = Math.min(150, s *  10.0 / an.frequencyBinCount);
		if (w[0x300] == 12) {
			c.fillRect(40+bin*32, 170-s, 16, s);
		}
		w[0x200 + 0x39 + bin] = s > 10 ? 5 : 7;
	}
}
_onRenderFrame = ROEngine.onRenderFrame;
ROEngine.onRenderFrame = function(data) { _onRenderFrame(data); render(document.getElementById("framebuffer").getContext("2d")); }

// MIDI output experiment, musical gates

var midi_send=function(l){}; navigator.requestMIDIAccess({software: true}).then(function (e) {for (let o of e.outputs) { midi_send = function(l) { o[1].send(l) }; return; }});
w=ROEngine.getGameMemory().world
var prev_state=[];
function update_gate(i) {
	var obj = 0x67 + i*3;
	var state = w[0x200 + obj] == 5;
	if (state != prev_state[i]) {
		midi_send([state ? 0x90 : 0x80, 0x24 + i, 0x7f]);
	}
	prev_state[i] = state;
}
_onRenderFrame = ROEngine.onRenderFrame;
ROEngine.onRenderFrame = function(data) { _onRenderFrame(data); for (var i=0;i<35;i++) update_gate(i); }

// Diffing memory in javascript

function diff(a,b) { for(var i =0; i<a.length;i++)if(a[i]!=b[i])console.log(i.toString(16),a[i].toString(16),b[i].toString(16)); }
function gamecopy() { var g=ROEngine.getGameMemory(); return { world: g.world.slice(), circuit: g.circuit.slice() }; }
function gamediff(a,b) { console.log("world"); diff(a.world, b.world); console.log("circuit"); diff(a.circuit, b.circuit); }
ref = gamecopy()
watch = setInterval( function() { console.log("\n\n"); gamediff(ref, gamecopy()) }, 1000 )

ROEngine.onRenderFrame = function(data) { _onRenderFrame(data); render(document.getElementById("framebuffer").getContext("2d")); }
w=ROEngine.getGameMemory().world
function render(c) {
	c.font='14px Futura'; c.fillStyle='rgba(190,190,255,0.8)';
	var current_room = w[0x300];
	for (var id=0; id<256; id++) {
		if (w[0x300+id] == current_room) {
			var x = w[0x400+id];
			var y = w[0x500+id];
			c.fillText(id.toString(16), 2*x, 192-y);
		}
	}
}

// Visual debugging, DOM style

f=document.getElementById("frame");
obj=[]; for (var i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
	f.appendChild(obj[i] = document.createElement("div"));
	obj[i].classList.add("layer");
	obj[i].style.display = "none";
	obj[i].style.font = "10px monospace";
	obj[i].style.color = "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7)";
	obj[i].style.background = "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)";
	obj[i].style.width = "auto";
	obj[i].style.height = "auto";
}
function update_obj(id) {
	var w=ROEngine.getGameMemory().world;
	var div = obj[id];
	var room = w[0x300];
	var x = w[0x400+id];
	var y = w[0x500+id];
	var sprite = w[0x100+id];
	var color = w[0x200+id];
	if (w[0x300+id] == room) {
		div.style.display = "block";
		div.style.left = (x*100/160.0) + "%";
		div.style.top = ((196-y-16 + (id%7))*100/200.0) + "%";
		div.innerText = `#${id.toString(16)} r=${room.toString(16)} spr=${sprite.toString(16)}, col=${color.toString(16)} (${x},${y})`;
	} else {
		div.style.display = "none";
	}
}
_onRenderFrame = ROEngine.onRenderFrame;
ROEngine.onRenderFrame = function(data) { _onRenderFrame(data); for (var i = 0; i < 256; i++) update_obj(i); }

// Mouse X coord to prototype chip pins?

_onRenderFrame = ROEngine.onRenderFrame;
_setMouseTracking = ROEngine.setMouseTracking;
w=ROEngine.getGameMemory().world
mousex = mousey = 0;
ROEngine.setMouseTracking = function (x, y) {
	mousex = x;
	mousey = y;
	_setMouseTracking(x, y);
}
inside_pins = [ 0x39, 0x3a, 0x3b, 0x3c, 0x40, 0x3f, 0x3e, 0x3d ];
outside_pins = [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 8, 7, 6, 5 ];
context = document.getElementById("framebuffer").getContext("2d");
ROEngine.onRenderFrame = function (data) {
	_onRenderFrame(data);
	var inside_byte = mousex & 0xff;
	var outside_byte = 0;
	for (var bit = 0; bit < 8; bit++) {
		w[0x200 + inside_pins[bit]] = (1 & (inside_byte >> bit)) ? 5 : 7;
		outside_byte |= (w[0x200 + outside_pins[bit]] == 5) << bit;
	}
	context.font = '30px Futura';
	context.fillStyle='#fff';
	context.fillText(outside_byte.toString(16), 25, 45);
}
